---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import CodeBlock from "../../components/CodeBlock.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  current="deployment"
  title="Deployment"
  description="Deploy torana as a docker-compose front door or a Kubernetes sidecar, with liveness/readiness probes wired into /healthz."
>
  <h1>Deployment</h1>
  <p class="docs-sub">Recipes for docker-compose and Kubernetes.</p>

  <h2>docker-compose front door</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    label="compose.yaml"
    copy={'services:\n  torana:\n    build: https://github.com/abhinavcdev/torana.git\n    ports: ["8080:8080"]\n    volumes: ["./torana.toml:/etc/torana/torana.toml:ro"]\n    depends_on: [app]\n  app:\n    image: your-app'}
  ><Fragment set:html={`services:
  torana:
    build: <span class="ac">https://github.com/abhinavcdev/torana.git</span>
    ports: [<span class="ac">"8080:8080"</span>]
    volumes: [<span class="ac">"./torana.toml:/etc/torana/torana.toml:ro"</span>]
    depends_on: [app]
  app:
    image: <span class="ac">your-app</span>`} /></CodeBlock>

  <h2>Kubernetes sidecar</h2>
  <p>Build the image from the repo Dockerfile, push it to your registry, and mount the config from a ConfigMap. Probes hit <code>/healthz</code>; graceful draining makes rolling restarts drop zero requests.</p>
  <CodeBlock
    label="pod spec (excerpt)"
    copy={'containers:\n  - name: app\n    image: your-app\n  - name: torana\n    image: your-registry/torana:latest\n    args: ["--config", "/etc/torana/torana.toml"]\n    ports:\n      - containerPort: 8080\n    volumeMounts:\n      - name: torana-config\n        mountPath: /etc/torana\n    livenessProbe:\n      httpGet: { path: /healthz, port: 9090 }\n    readinessProbe:\n      httpGet: { path: /healthz, port: 9090 }\nvolumes:\n  - name: torana-config\n    configMap:\n      name: torana-config'}
  ><Fragment set:html={`containers:
  - name: app
    image: <span class="ac">your-app</span>
  - name: torana
    image: <span class="ac">your-registry/torana:latest</span>
    args: [<span class="ac">"--config"</span>, <span class="ac">"/etc/torana/torana.toml"</span>]
    ports:
      - containerPort: 8080
    volumeMounts:
      - name: torana-config
        mountPath: /etc/torana
    livenessProbe:
      httpGet: { path: <span class="ac">/healthz</span>, port: 9090 }
    readinessProbe:
      httpGet: { path: <span class="ac">/healthz</span>, port: 9090 }
volumes:
  - name: torana-config
    configMap:
      name: <span class="ac">torana-config</span>`} /></CodeBlock>

  <div class="callout">Expose <code>metrics_addr</code> as <code>0.0.0.0:9090</code> inside containers so probes and scrapers can reach it; keep it on <code>127.0.0.1</code> when the proxy shares a network namespace with its scraper.</div>

  <h2>Bare VPS with systemd</h2>
  <p>No container runtime needed: torana is a static binary, so a plain systemd unit is the whole story. Run it as a dedicated non-root user and grant <code>CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE</code> instead of root when binding <code>:443</code> directly.</p>
  <CodeBlock
    label="/etc/systemd/system/torana.service"
    copy={'[Service]\nUser=torana\nGroup=torana\nExecStart=/usr/local/bin/torana --config /etc/torana/torana.toml\nExecReload=/bin/kill -HUP $MAINPID\nRestart=on-failure\nAmbientCapabilities=CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE\nCapabilityBoundingSet=CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE\nNoNewPrivileges=true\nProtectSystem=strict\nReadWritePaths=/var/lib/torana'}
  ><Fragment set:html={`[Service]
User=torana
Group=torana
ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/torana --config /etc/torana/torana.toml
ExecReload=/bin/kill -HUP $MAINPID
Restart=on-failure
AmbientCapabilities=CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE
CapabilityBoundingSet=CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE
NoNewPrivileges=true
ProtectSystem=strict
ReadWritePaths=/var/lib/torana`} /></CodeBlock>
  <p>A full working example — a real static frontend and a separate API backend, both proxied through one <code>torana.toml</code>, with systemd units for all three and a step-by-step guide from a $4/mo VPS to a browser-trusted certificate — lives in <a href="https://github.com/abhinavcdev/torana/tree/main/examples/full-stack-demo">examples/full-stack-demo</a> in the repo.</p>

  <p>Next: <a href="../benchmarking/">benchmarking</a>.</p>
</DocsLayout>
